## 📌 List Interface (java.util)
### Key Implementations
- **ArrayList** → Dynamic array, fast random access  
- **LinkedList** → Doubly linked list, fast insertion/deletion  
- **Vector** → Legacy synchronized list  

### Core Methods
| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `add(E e)` | Add element |
| `add(int index, E e)` | Insert at index |
| `get(int index)` | Access element |
| `set(int index, E e)` | Update element |
| `remove(int index)` | Remove by index |
| `remove(Object o)` | Remove by value |
| `size()` | Current size |
| `isEmpty()` | Check empty |
| `contains(Object o)` | Search |
| `indexOf(Object o)` | First occurrence |
| `lastIndexOf(Object o)` | Last occurrence |
| `clear()` | Remove all |
| `toArray()` | Convert to array |
| `iterator()` | Get iterator |
| `listIterator()` | Bidirectional iterator |
| `subList(int from, int to)` | Extract portion |

